="h5 side-accordion__title">Applicants with recent secondary education </p> <div class="side-accordion__content"> <p>You’ll need to meet the minimum entry requirements and subject prerequisites for your chosen course. </p><p>If your school result was affected by circumstances outside of your control, such as financial hardship, illness, disability or a challenging home environment, you may qualify for an access scheme. You can apply through your TAC as part of your application process. </p><p><a href="https://www.acu.edu.au/study-at-acu/admission-pathways/i-did-not-get-the-atar-op-rank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit;" target="_blank">Learn more about access schemes</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="side-accordion" id="applicants-with-vocational-education-and-training"> <p style="font-weight: bold;" class="h5 side-accordion__title">Applicants with vocational education and training (VET) study</p> <div class="side-accordion__content"> <p>You’ll need to meet the minimum entry requirements and subject prerequisites for your chosen course. </p><p><strong>For current year 12 students</strong> </p><p>If you’re a current Year 12 applicant you can be given a selection rank separate from, and in addition to, your ATAR if you’ve completed a competency-based and graded <a href="https://www.acu.edu.au/study-at-acu/find-a-course/uni-terminology-explained" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AQF</a> Certificate III or above. </p><p><strong>For non-school leavers</strong></p><p>If you’ve completed, or are completing a competency-based <a href="https://www.acu.edu.au/study-at-acu/find-a-course/uni-terminology-explained" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AQF</a> Certificate IV or <a href="https://www.acu.edu.au/study-at-acu/find-a-course/uni-terminology-explained" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AQF</a> diploma you will be assigned a selection rank by your local Tertiary Admission Centre (TAC). This is an entry score based on your individual